{"id":34471,"date":"2020-10-19T21:41:13","date_gmt":"2020-10-19T17:41:13","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34471"},"modified":"2022-10-25T12:37:38","modified_gmt":"2022-10-25T08:37:38","slug":"prophet-swears-on-three","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/10\/19\/prophet-swears-on-three\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Islam: The Prophet swears upon four truths"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>I swear an oath upon three truths. Allah Almighty does not make one with a share in Islam like one without. The shares of Islam are three: prayer, fasting, and charity. Allah Almighty will not take a servant as an ally in this world but entrust him to another on the Day of Resurrection. And a man does not love a people but that Allah will resurrect him with them. The fourth, if I were to swear upon it, I hope it would not be sinful: Allah Almighty does not conceal the sins of a servant in the world but that He will conceal them on the Day of Resurrection<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 25121<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e <strong>\u062b\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u062b\u064c \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0644\u0650\u0641\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0632\